prepareWindows

public static void prepareWindows(AHost host,
                                  ConsoleManager cm,
                                  PhpBuild build,
                                  boolean enable_debug_prompt)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
for Windows hosts, does the following: -if enable_debug_prompt is true, enables Windows Error Reporting popup messages, if enable_debug_prompt is false then disables Windows Error Reporting -typically, for manual use enable_debug_prompt should be true and for automated use enable_debug_prompt should be false. Windows Error Reporting popups will interfere with automated testing -disables firewall, for network services like SOAP, HTTP, etc... -creates a php-sdk share pointing to %SYSTEMDRIVE%\\php-sdk -installs VC runtime If enable_debug_prompt and if WinDebug is installed, enables it for debugging PHP.

host -
cm -
build -
enable_debug_prompt -

installVCRuntime

public static void installVCRuntime(AHost host,
                                    ConsoleManager cm,
                                    PhpBuild build)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                                    java.io.IOException,
                                    java.lang.Exception
PHP on Windows requires Microsoft's VC Runtime to be installed. This method ensures that the correct version is installed. PHP 5.3 and 5.4 require the VC9 x86 Runtime PHP 5.5+ require the VC11 x86 Runtime Windows 7+ already has the VC9 x86 Runtime Windows 8+ already has the VC11 x86 Runtime

checks if a registry key matches the given value. if it does, returns true. if not, asks user for privilege elevation and changes the registry key. returns false only if key could not be changed to value.
